"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0802-1463252-paris-2024-irish-in-action-on-day-8-of-olympic-games\", \"text\": \"Ireland will have two Olympic gold medallists in action on Saturday at Paris 2024, with Daniel Wiffen taking to the blocks in the heats of the 1500m freestyle and Kellie Harrington facing off against Beatriz Soares Ferreira in a bout to see which fighter will box for lightweight gold.  Danielle Hill will join Wiffen at La Defense for the heats of 50m freestyle, while Ireland are also in relay action in the pool.  Shane Lowry and Rory McIlroy play the penultimate round of the golf tournament at Le Golf National, with the latter still in contention for a medal.  Ben Healy and Ryan Mullen get on their bikes for the road race, with Finn Lynch, Eve McMahon, Madison Corcoran, Noel Hendrick and Liam Jegou all racing in boats of various descriptions.  Double world champion Rhys McClenaghan bids for gold in the final of the pommel horse, with 1500m runners Luke McCann, Cathal Doyle and Andrew Coscoran bidding to bounce back from disappointing displays when they contest the repechage of the event.  Saturday 3 August  (In order of start time)  GOLF  0855Men's singles round 3:Shane Lowry  1044Men's singles round 3:Rory McIlroy  CYCLING  1000Men's road race:Ben Healy and Ryan Mullen  SWIMMING  1000-1025Women's 50m freestyle heat 8:Danielle Hill  1025-1133Men's 1500m freestyle heat 3:Daniel Wiffen  1133-1144Men's 4x100m medley relay heat 2:Conor Ferguson, Darragh Greene, Max McCusker and Shane Ryan  1144-1156Women's 4x100m medley relay heat 2:Danielle Hill, Mona McSharry, Ellen Walshe and TBC  1937-1949Women's 50m freestyle semi-finals:Danielle Hill(if qualified)  SAILING  1110-1206Men's dinghy race 5:Finn Lynch  1223-1314Men's dinghy race 6:Finn Lynch  1325-1416Women's dinghy race 5:Eve McMahon  1421-1517Women's dinghy race 6:Eve McMahon  CANOE SLALOM  1430-1525Women's kayak cross round 1 race 10:Madison Corcoran  1540-1635Men's kayak cross round 1 race 3:Noel Hendrick  1540-1635Men's kayak cross round 1 race 7:Liam Jegou  1705-1730Women's kayak cross repechage 1:Madison Corcoran(if applicable)  1745-1810Men's kayak cross repechage:Noel Hendrick, Liam Jegou(if applicable)  GYMNASTICS  1610-1650Men's pommel horse final:Rhys McClenaghan  ATHLETICS  1815-1830Men's 1500m repechage heat 1:Luke McCann, Cathal Doyle  1815-1830Men's 1500m repechage heat 2:Andrew Coscoran  BOXING  2108Women's 60kg (lightweight) semi-final:Kellie Harringtonv Beatriz Soares Ferreira (Bra)    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"